../../../beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-006/attacks/chain-01.md:96:What is weak is the underlying bet: that one can distill enough of the pressure-coupled tensor dynamics into a robust observable to gain coercive control. That is precisely the compression that earlier tensor and pressure-structure routes have repeatedly failed to make decisive. The most credible output here is therefore not a proposition-scale regularity mechanism, but a sharper obstruction memo explaining why the pressure-Hessian route remains structurally informative and yet analytically nonclosing once the full nonlocal debt is paid.
