+# Meta Note - Step 009 Exploration 001
+
+Endpoint-first pressure-Hessian branches must separate theorem endpoints from
+mechanism language at the first gate.
+
+Reusable lesson:
+
+- `full stretching control`,
+  `pressure-Hessian/strain defect control`,
+  and
+  `harmonic-moment cancellation`
+  are not equal theorem endpoints on their own;
+- the branch needs one inherited contradiction ledger first;
+- and tensor language is only admissible if it changes the exact live bad term
+  inside that ledger rather than renaming the bottleneck.
+
+For this mission step, the only locally frozen theorem ledger is still the
+inherited suitable-weak / Leray-Hopf plus LEI, CKN/Lin epsilon-regularity
+package with `I_p^far` as the pressure-side obstruction. That rule prevents the
+branch from surviving on pressure-Hessian branding alone.
diff --git a/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/meta-inbox/meta-step-009-exploration-002.md b/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/meta-inbox/meta-step-009-exploration-002.md
